description: From toxemia (“organic blood poisoning”) +‎ -ic, from New Latin toxaemia, from Ancient Greek τοξικόν (toxikón, “poison, toxin”) + αἷμα (haîma, “blood”).

adjectives.description: toxemic (comparative more toxemic, superlative most toxemic)

entries.meaning: affected by or otherwise relating to toxemia, organically poisoned
